  "title": "Associate Professor",
  "department": "Bachelor of Science, Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)",
  "school": "",
  "profile_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/faculty/t-m-abul-kalam-azad-phd",
  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/T.%20M.%20Abul%20Kalam%20Azad.jpg?itok=02DcT__L",
  "bio_raw": "T. M. Abul Kalam Azad has more than 25 years teaching experience at home & abroad. Currently, I am working as an Associate Professor in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB). Before joining ULAB, I had taught at Asia pacific University as adjunct faculty for one semester and next taught at East West University for one semester. I taught at Bangladesh International School & College, Jeddah(BISCJ) for Nine years. Also, I taught at Rajshahi University of Engineering and Technology (RUET) for Six years.\nT. M. Abul Kalam Azad has earned PhD degree from the Department of Mathematics, Jahangirnagar University. My research interest is computational fluid Dynamics and research work concentrated on the study of the pollutant behavior in the fluid media. I have completed my Master of Philosophy(MPil) in Pure Mathematics, Master of Science in Pure Mathematics from Rajshahi University and Bachelor of Science (Honors) in Pure Mathematics from Rajshahi University.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Computational Fluid Dynamics, Numerical Analysis, Differential Equations, Statistics and Probability, Business Mathematics and Stock Market Analysis."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD\ndegree from the Department of Mathematics, Jahangirnagar University.\nMaster of Philosophy (MPil)\nin Pure Mathematics, Rajshahi University\nMaster of Science\nin Pure Mathematics, Rajshahi University\nBachelor of Science (Honors)\nin Pure Mathematics, Rajshahi University"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nT M A K Azad, A C Paul, “Jacobson Radical for Gamma Rings”, Rajshahi Univ. stud.,part-B, J.Sci. 1997, Vol.25, ISSN 1681-0708.\nDate: 04/15/1997\nT M A K Azad\n, A C Paul, “Artinian Γ-Rings”, Southeast Asian Bulletin of Mathematics (1999)  23:  pg. 271-275\nSpringer-Verlag 1999, Hong-Kong.\nDate: 11/03/1999\nT M A K Azad,\nL S Andallah, “An Explicit Finite Difference Method”, ulab journal of science and engineering, Vol. 6, No. 1, pg. 32-37, Nov. 2015.  ISSN 2079-4398.\nDate: 11/03/2015\nT M A K Azad\n, M Begum, L S Andallah, “An explicit finite difference scheme for advection diffusion equation”, jahangirnagar journal of mathematics and mathematical sciences, Vol.-24, pg. 67-75, 2015, ISSN  2219-5823.\nDate: 12/01/2015\nT M A K Azad\nand L S Andallah, “Numerical Study on the stability of Finite Difference Schemes for Solving Advection diffusion equation”, ulab journal of science and Eng., Vol.7, pg. 3-11, No. 1, Nov. 2016 ISSN 2079-4398\nDate: 11/03/2016\nT M A K Azad\nand L S Andallah, “Stability analysis of finite difference schemes for an advection diffusion equation”, Bangladesh J. Sci. Res. 29, No.2: 143-151, 2016 (Dec.), ISSN 0253-5432.\nDate: 12/14/2016\nT M A K Azad\n, “Estimation of River Pollutant by Explicit Finite Difference Scheme for the Advection Diffusion Equation”, Jahangirnagar University Journal of Science, Vol.-40, No. 1, pg.103-116, 2017, ISSN  1022-8594.\nDate: 11/08/2017\nT M A K Azad,\n“A Comparison of Some Numerical Schemes for Modified Advection Diffusion Equation”, ulab journal of science and Eng. Vol.-9, pg. 33-41, No. 1, Nov. 2018,\nISSN 2079-4398.\nDate: 11/06/2018",
    "Conference Proceedings\n18th International Mathematics Conference of Bangladesh Mathematical Society, 20-22 March 2014, IUB, Dhaka.\nDate: 03/04/2014\n19th International Mathematics Conference of Bangladesh Mathematical Society, 18-20 December, 2015, Brac University, Dhaka. Delivered talk titled “Estimation of River Pollutant by Explicit Finite Difference Scheme for the Advection Diffusion Equation”\nDate: 12/18/2015\n20th International Mathematics Conference 2017, 08-10 December 2017, University of Dhaka. Delivered talk titled “Numerical Solution of Convection Diffusion Equation”.\nDate: 12/08/2017\n3rd International Joint Conference on Computational Intelligence (IJCCI 2019), 25-26 October,2019, ULAB, Dhaka.\nDate: 10/25/2019"
